02/03/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- According to General Prosecutor Theodhori Sollaku, the crime rate in Albania rose in 2004, up 18 per cent compared to the previous year. Press reports Wednesday (2 March) cited the prosecutor's annual report, which notes the number of cases related to organised crime, trafficking and corruption jumped last year.
In other news, Albania is negotiating to secure $48m in loans from the World Bank and the EBRD to upgrade its electricity distribution system. The state-run Electro-energy Corporation expects to sign deals with the two institutions later this month. (Albanian News, AP - 02/03/05)
